This article is a message from President Barack Obama to Congress regarding the budget for the fiscal year 2010. The budget outlines the administration's plans to address the economic crisis and promote long-term economic growth. It emphasizes investments in education, healthcare reform, and renewable energy. The budget also focuses on fiscal discipline and aims to rein in unsustainable deficits and debt. The administration has identified programs that should be terminated or changed, resulting in savings of nearly $17 billion. The budget includes savings from ending subsidies for oil and gas companies and eliminating entitlements to banks and lenders for student loans. It also includes investments in national security, military rebuilding, and diplomatic efforts. The president acknowledges that there will be opposition to certain aspects of the budget, but believes that Americans are ready to embrace shared responsibilities and rebuild the economy.